    <system:String x:Key="Help_Description">A powerful desktop AI assistant with RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) capabilities, local embeddings, and document analysis.</system:String>
    
    <system:String x:Key="Help_GettingStarted">Getting Started</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_GettingStarted_Text">1. Go to Settings and configure your API key (OpenRouter or compatible API)
2. Start chatting in the Chat tab
3. Optionally, add documents to the Knowledge Base for RAG-enhanced responses</system:String>
    
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Features">Features</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Feature_Chat">Chat - Conversation with AI models with streaming responses</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Feature_KB">Knowledge Base - Import documents (PDF, DOCX, TXT, MD, JSON, CSV) and use them as context for AI responses</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Feature_DocAnalysis">Document Analysis - Analyze documents for summaries, key points, and compliance checks</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Feature_Embeddings">Embeddings - Download and use local embedding models for offline vector search</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Feature_RAG">RAG System - Hybrid retrieval combining vector search and keyword search with RRF fusion</system:String>
    
    <system:String x:Key="Help_RAG">RAG System</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_RAG_Text">The RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) system enhances AI responses by retrieving relevant context from your documents:
‚Ä¢ Vector Search - Semantic similarity using embeddings
‚Ä¢ Keyword Search - Full-text search (FTS5) for exact matches
‚Ä¢ Hybrid Mode - Combines both methods using Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF)
‚Ä¢ Flight Recorder - Debug panel showing sources, candidates, and timing</system:String>
    
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Embeddings">Local Embeddings</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="Help_Embeddings_Text">Download embedding models to generate vectors locally without API calls:
1. Go to Embeddings tab
2. Download a model (recommended: Multilingual E5 Large Instruct)
3. Click "Load selected model"
4. Enable "Use local embeddings" in Settings</system:String>
    
